---
title: Shrimp, Bacon & Asparagus Cavatappi with Grape Tomatoes, Basil & Parmesan
description: This pasta dish has a quick trick we love: cooking asparagus and grape tomatoes in smoky bacon fat after sizzling bacon to crisp perfection. Toss those veggies with curly cavatappi in creamy basil sauce, then bring it all home with chopped bacon, shredded Parmesan, and a sprinkle of chili flakes for a savory meal that’s sure to satisfy.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6864c3565e6b2bfce953a99b-5d0ed423.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6864c3565e6b2bfce953a99b-en-US.pdf
course: main course
cuisine: Southern Europe
servings: 2
time required: 20 minutes
author: HelloFresh
nutrition:
  calories: 970 kcal
  fat: 54 g
  saturated fat: 20 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 8 g
  protein: 42 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1490 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/shrimp-bacon-and-asparagus-cavatappi-6864c3565e6b2bfce953a99b
---

Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Heat a large dry pan over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%ounce}; cook, turning
occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy,
~{6-10%minutes}. 
> TIP: Add a drizzle of oil if your bacon is not crisping.

Turn off heat; transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate. Reserve 1 TBSP bacon
fat in a small #bowl. Wipe out pan with paper towels. Once bacon is cool enough
to handle, roughly chop.

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

While pasta cooks, halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}. Trim and discard woody
bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}; cut stalks crosswise into 1-inch pieces.

Heat reserved bacon fat and a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in pan used for bacon
over medium-high heat. Add tomatoes, asparagus, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and
@pepper{pinch}.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until asparagus is bright green, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and add @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @basil paste{1%ounce},
½ cup reserved pasta cooking water, @butter{2%tablespoon}, and @sugar{¼%tsp}.

> For 4 servings, use 1 cup pasta cooking water, 4 TBSP butter, and ½ tsp sugar.

Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring constantly, until butter has melted,
~{1-2%minutes}.

Add drained cavatappi and toss until thoroughly coated. 
> TIP: Add extra splashes of reserved pasta cooking water for saucier pasta.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

Divide pasta between #bowls and top with bacon, @parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon},
and as many @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Serve.

> Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.